The twelfth prebend was that of the Three Choristers. Its revenues were to be divided equally among its possessors: and of these, one was to be chosen by the bailies and council of the city, and two, by the Provost of the College3 by whom all three were to be instituted, after diligent examination of their qualifications made by the prebendaries of the ehurch. The youths were to be well and carefully instructed by the third prebendary, or Master of the Song Sehool, in the Gregorian ebant,3
